The paper discusses the shift-invariance properties of the dual-tree complex wavelet transform, which is a common tool in signal processing and image analysis. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), speech processing (cs.SP), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision (cs.CV). Among these, cs.IT and cs.SI are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on the mathematical properties of the transform and its relationship to the fractional Hilbert transform. However, the paper also discusses applications of the transform to image analysis and multi-dimensional signal processing, which could make cs.CV a relevant category as well.
